The `listChangedFiles` function is missing staged files. In a `pre-commit` hook, the files being committed are in the index (staged). Without including `--cached` in the git diff, these files will be ignored by the formatter. Additionally, combining committed, staged, and unstaged files ensures the script works correctly across different developer workflows.

```javascript
  const staged = runGit(['diff', '--name-only', '--cached', '--diff-filter=ACMR']);
  const unstaged = runGit(['diff', '--name-only', '--diff-filter=ACMR']);

  return new Set(
    [
      ...(committed?.split('\n') ?? []),
      ...(staged?.split('\n') ?? []),
      ...(unstaged?.split('\n') ?? [])
    ]
```

